Here’s exactly what you need — a clean block that renames the desired columns and drops the extras:

# Rename the columns you want to keep
merged_df.rename(columns={
    'PLAYER_NAME_x': 'PLAYER_NAME',
    'START_POSITION_x': 'START_POSITION',
    'GAME_DATE_x': 'GAME_DATE'
}, inplace=True)

# Drop the duplicate/unwanted columns
merged_df.drop(columns=['PLAYER_NAME_y', 'START_POSITION_y', 'GAME_DATE_y', 'TEAM_ID_y'], inplace=True, errors='ignore')

After this, your merged_df will be cleaned up and ready with the correct column names:
	•	PLAYER_NAME
	•	START_POSITION
	•	GAME_DATE
	•	TEAM_ID

Let me know if you want to automatically handle this kind of cleanup for other suffix conflicts in the future.